    	<h2><a name="2002-11-20" href="#2002-11-20"><font color="#660000">2002-11-20</font></a></h2>
   	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="84841586">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<h1>Distributed Collaborative Systems</h1><h2>Cyberspace</h2><h3>Convergence on ubiquitous objects</h3><a href="http://www.gridcomputingplanet.com/news/print/0,,3281_1500801,00.html">Grid Computing Planet: News: Internet, Grid To Forge Brave New Computing World</a>.&nbsp; PriceWaterhouseCoopers predicts that there will be a convergence of grid computing, computing as a utility, voice-over-Internet, and pervasive/ubiquitous computing.&nbsp; Three key enablers are considered to be the increase in commodity-technology capabilities, scalalbe computing and communications infrastructures, and flexibility-reliability-manageability of those infrastructures.&nbsp; It is claimed that grid computing will solve inter-enterprise problems.<br /><br />It would seem that we quickly need a better model of what can be counted on for distributed operation, especially in the area of trusted computation.<br>
